## 🏗️ PROJECT STRUCTURE

Feature-based structure — strictly enforced:

```
src/
  app/                        # Next.js App Router
    (auth)/                   # route groups
    (dashboard)/
  features/                   # feature modules
    [feature]/
      components/             # UI components only
      actions/                # server actions and business logic
      helpers/                # utility functions and hooks
      types/
  components/
    ui/                       # shadcn/ui components
    shared/                   # shared components
  lib/                        # core config (prisma, etc.)
  helpers/                    # global helpers & utils
  types/                      # global types
```

### 📌 Folder Structure Rules
- Every new feature or route **must** follow the structure above
- If a folder does **not exist** → create it + add a `README.md` explaining its purpose
- If a folder **exists** → ensure each file is in the correct subfolder
- Never place files outside their designated folder

