## 📐 CODE RULES

### General
- TypeScript only — no `any`, no `unknown`, no type casting unless unavoidable
- Always define explicit return types for functions and components
- Prettier + ESLint enforced — no warnings, no errors
- Follow SOLID principles — single responsibility, no god components

### Naming Conventions
- Variables & functions: `camelCase`
- Components & files: `PascalCase`
- Constants: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE`
- Types & interfaces: `PascalCase` — no `I` prefix
- Folders: `kebab-case`

### Component Rules
- Server Components by default
- `"use client"` only when required: interactivity, hooks, browser APIs
- Keep components small and focused — split when doing more than one thing
- No inline styles — Tailwind only
- Always add `loading.tsx` with shadcn Skeleton for every route
- Always add `error.tsx` for error boundaries on routes

### TypeScript Rules
```typescript
// ✅ Good
type UserRole = "admin" | "user" | "moderator";
interface CreateUserInput {
  name: string;
  email: string;
  role: UserRole;
}

// ❌ Bad
const data: any = {};
const user: unknown = getUser();
```

