## 🎨 UI & DESIGN (Senior UX Standards)

As a senior UI/UX engineer, every interface decision must be intentional and based on UX principles — not personal taste.

### Component Library
- shadcn/ui as base — customize via `cn()` and CVA variants
- Never `!important` on shadcn styles
- Follow existing import and variant patterns — no new dependencies without explicit request

### UX Principles (Non-Negotiable)
- **Visual Hierarchy:** most important = largest/boldest — guide the eye
- **Color Psychology:** every color choice must serve a purpose
- **Whitespace:** generous spacing = readability + trust
- **Consistency:** same interaction patterns across the entire product
- **Feedback:** every user action needs a response — loading, success, error states always
- **Accessibility:** `aria-label`, keyboard nav, WCAG AA contrast minimum
- **Mobile-first:** design for smallest screen first, scale up

### Tailwind Best Practices
```tsx
// ✅ Conditional classes via cn()
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";
<div className={cn("base-class", isActive && "active-class", className)} />

// ✅ Brand colors via CSS variables in tailwind.config
// ❌ Never arbitrary hex inline: text-[#ff0000]
```

---

## 🔐 AUTH & SECURITY

- Custom auth or JWT via secure HTTP-only cookies
- Verify auth server-side on every request — no client-side trust
- Never trust client-sent user IDs — always derive from server-side session
- Zod validation on all inputs before DB operations
- All secrets in environment variables — never hardcode

